<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFF3FF92FF409529DCCAFA08" blockId="7.[178,1085,1301,1469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">
C o m m e n t: 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFF3FF92FE9B9529DC2FFA9E" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[361,592,1301,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFF3FF92FE9B9529DC2FFA9E" box="[361,592,1301,1323]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">Acanthoglossa punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a single male from &quot; 
<collectingRegion id="4986F857FFF3FF92FF48950EDF62FAFD" box="[186,285,1330,1352]" country="Tunisia" name="Kairouan" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">Kairouan</collectingRegion>
, inondations, 10 (Dr Normand)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFF3FF92FD75950EDD65FAFD" author="FAUVEL A" box="[647,794,1330,1352]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" pagination="250" refId="ref5972" refString="FAUVEL A. (1901): Acanthoglossa n. sp., de Tunisie. - Revue d'Entomologie 20: 250." type="journal article" year="1901">FAUVEL 1901</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="54F98817FFF3FF92FC90950EDDC4FAFD" box="[866,955,1330,1352]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">holotype</typeStatus>
was looked for, but found neither in the Fauvel collection at the IRSNB nor in the collections of the MNHNP (GÉRARD e-mail 29 June, 2009; TAGHAVIAN e-mail 29 June, 2009), suggesting that it is probably lost. All that was found is an 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFF3FF92FD4F95B6DDDEFA15" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[701,929,1418,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFF3FF92FD4F95B6DDDEFA15" box="[701,929,1418,1440]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">Acanthoglossa punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
label (without specimen) in the Jarrige collection at the MNHNP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFF3FF92FF4095F1DD04F98E" blockId="7.[178,1085,1485,1595]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFF3FF92FE3B95F1DC29FA56" authorityName=", JARRIGE" authorityYear="1958" box="[457,598,1485,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFF3FF92FE3B95F1DC29FA56" box="[457,598,1485,1507]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">A. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single male 
<typeStatus id="54F98817FFF3FF92FC9195F1DDC3FA56" box="[867,956,1485,1507]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">holotype</typeStatus>
from &quot;st. 32 bis, Jardin du Beylik à Djanet&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFF3FF92FDF495D6DCE5F9B5" author="JARRIGE J" box="[518,666,1514,1536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref6043" refString="JARRIGE J. (1958): Coleopteres brachelytres recoltes au Tassili n'Ajjer par la mission de 1949. - Traveaux de l'Institut du Recherches Sahariennes (Serie de Tassili) 3: 87 - 107." type="journal article" year="1958">JARRIGE 1958</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen was looked for, but not found in the collections of the MNHNP (TAGHAVIAN pers. comm.). The above female is the only specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFF3FF92FE799619DC67F98E" authorityName=", JARRIGE" authorityYear="1958" box="[395,536,1573,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFF3FF92FE799619DC67F98E" box="[395,536,1573,1595]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1168">A. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in the Jarrige collection.
</paragraph>
