<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFCFF9DFF4095E4DA43F9FD" blockId="8.[178,1085,1496,1608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169">
In the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFCFF9DFE0495E4DD42FA5B" authority=", JARRIGE (1958)" authorityName=", JARRIGE" authorityYear="1958" box="[502,829,1496,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFCFF9DFE0495E4DCF8FA5B" box="[502,647,1496,1518]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169">A. deserticola</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFFCFF9DFD6895E4DD42FA5B" author="JARRIGE J" box="[666,829,1496,1518]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref6043" refString="JARRIGE J. (1958): Coleopteres brachelytres recoltes au Tassili n'Ajjer par la mission de 1949. - Traveaux de l'Institut du Recherches Sahariennes (Serie de Tassili) 3: 87 - 107." type="journal article" year="1958">JARRIGE (1958)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
provides distinguishing characters separating the species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFCFF9DFDB695CADCA6F9B9" authorityName=": SMETANA" authorityYear="2004" box="[580,729,1526,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFCFF9DFDB695CADCA6F9B9" box="[580,729,1526,1548]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169">A. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but remarkably there is no reference whatsoever to 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFCFF9DFE739628DF9DF99F" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[385,482,1556,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFCFF9DFE739628DF9DF99F" box="[385,482,1556,1578]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1169">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which leads to the conclusion that he may not have been aware of this species. An examination of the specimen listed above and identified by
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF4090E7DC05FE98" blockId="9.[178,1087,219,301]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
Jarrige as 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFEEC90E7DFD3FF44" authorityName=", JARRIGE" authorityYear="1958" box="[286,428,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFEEC90E7DFD3FF44" box="[286,428,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it perfectly matches the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFBDA90E7DE88FEBA" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFBDA90E7DE88FEBA" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that both names refer to the same species and that, consequently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFBD490C5DF5DFE98" authorityName=", JARRIGE" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFBD490C5DF5DFE98" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFDE1912BDC0BFE98" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[531,628,279,301]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFDE1912BDC0BFE98" box="[531,628,279,301]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF409102DC9BFE79" blockId="9.[178,1087,318,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
Based on the detailed illustrations of the aedeagus provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFFDFF9CFCBF9102DD96FEE1" author="JARRIGE J" box="[845,1001,318,340]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref6043" refString="JARRIGE J. (1958): Coleopteres brachelytres recoltes au Tassili n'Ajjer par la mission de 1949. - Traveaux de l'Institut du Recherches Sahariennes (Serie de Tassili) 3: 87 - 107." type="journal article" year="1958">JARRIGE (1958</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1), there is little doubt that 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFE5C9160DC6EFEC4" authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1901" box="[430,529,348,370]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punica">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFE5C9160DC6EFEC4" box="[430,529,348,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. punica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFD2D9160DD37FEC4" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Fauvel" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[735,840,348,370]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientis">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFD2D9160DD37FEC4" box="[735,840,348,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. orientis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFCA59160DD94FEC7" authorityName=": SMETANA" authorityYear="2004" box="[855,1003,348,370]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipennis">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFCA59160DD94FEC7" box="[855,1003,348,370]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. longipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFBDA9160DE9CFE25" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFBDA9160DE9CFE25" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The general morphology of the aedeagus, particularly the shape of the ventral process and the internal structures are highly similar. Externally, the species is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="54F98817FFFDFF9CFF25918BDF7CFE79" box="[215,259,439,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFE86918ADC76FE79" box="[372,521,438,460]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFE86918ADC76FE79" box="[372,521,438,460]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Acanthoglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C424D36FFFDFF9CFDE7918ADC1DFE79" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1859" box="[533,610,438,460]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Acanthoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis id="B936EAA7FFFDFF9CFDE7918ADC1DFE79" box="[533,610,438,460]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">A. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF4091E1DD3EFDA5" blockId="9.[178,1085,476,528]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
D i a g n o s i s: Body length 
<quantity id="4CBA9B50FFFDFF9CFE0C91E0DC36FE47" box="[510,585,476,498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="13792A30FFFDFF9CFD1C91E0DD4BFE47" box="[750,820,476,498]" captionStart="Figs 14-21" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1393,1413]" captionTargetBox="[183,1085,218,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-0@8.[178,1085,215,1385]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 14-21: Acanthoglossa punica FAUVEL from Chad (14-15), A. crassa COIFFAIT, holotype (16- 17), and Hypomedon niloticus (KOCH) (18-21): (14, 16, 18) habitus; (15, 17, 19) forebody; (20) male sternite VIII; (21) aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 14, 16, 18: 1.0 mm; 15, 17, 19: 0.5 mm; 20-21: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276557/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
. Coloration: whole body reddish, with the elytra, legs, and antennae paler reddish-yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF40921CDC0FFD5E" blockId="9.[178,1085,544,747]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
Head (
<figureCitation id="13792A30FFFDFF9CFF0B921CDF38FD83" box="[249,327,544,566]" captionStart="Figs 14-21" captionStartId="8.[178,218,1393,1413]" captionTargetBox="[183,1085,218,1368]" captionTargetId="figure-0@8.[178,1085,215,1385]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 14-21: Acanthoglossa punica FAUVEL from Chad (14-15), A. crassa COIFFAIT, holotype (16- 17), and Hypomedon niloticus (KOCH) (18-21): (14, 16, 18) habitus; (15, 17, 19) forebody; (20) male sternite VIII; (21) aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 14, 16, 18: 1.0 mm; 15, 17, 19: 0.5 mm; 20-21: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276557/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) 1.14 times as wide as long, weakly dilated posteriad; lateral margins behind eyes almost straight, posterior angles marked; posterior margin distinctly concave in the middle; punctation coarse, areolate, and very dense, slightly less dense in median dorsal area; interstices narrow, much narrower than diameter of punctures, without microsculpture; pubescence moderately long and erect to suberect; eyes strongly convex, slightly less than half as long as postocular region in dorsal view; labrum not dentate, with small V-shaped excision in the middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF4092C7DD3DFCF8" blockId="9.[178,1085,763,845]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Pronotum approximately 1.2 times as wide as long, widest across anterior angles, and 0.95 times as wide as head; punctation similar to that of head, extremely dense; interstices reduced to narrow ridges; pubescence similar to that of head.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF409361DC3EFC78" blockId="9.[178,1084,861,973]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Elytra approximately as long, and 1.2 times as wide as pronotum. Metatarsomere I as long as the combined length of II and III. Abdomen approximately 0.9 times as wide as elytra, widest at segment VI; segment VI approximately twice as long as segment V; tergite VII with narrow palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF4093E2DCC2FBA4" blockId="9.[178,1085,989,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
3: according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFFDFF9CFE8193E2DC74FC46" author="JARRIGE J" box="[371,523,989,1011]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref6043" refString="JARRIGE J. (1958): Coleopteres brachelytres recoltes au Tassili n'Ajjer par la mission de 1949. - Traveaux de l'Institut du Recherches Sahariennes (Serie de Tassili) 3: 87 - 107." type="journal article" year="1958">JARRIGE 1958</bibRefCitation>
, posterior margin of sternite VIII deeply excised; aedeagus as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD34B44FFFDFF9CFE4993C0DC2BFBA4" author="JARRIGE J" box="[443,596,1019,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170" pagination="87 - 107" refId="ref6043" refString="JARRIGE J. (1958): Coleopteres brachelytres recoltes au Tassili n'Ajjer par la mission de 1949. - Traveaux de l'Institut du Recherches Sahariennes (Serie de Tassili) 3: 87 - 107." type="journal article" year="1958">JARRIGE (1958</bibRefCitation>
: figure 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD36B5FFFDFF9CFF40941EDD45FBC1" blockId="9.[178,1085,1057,1140]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: This species was previously known only from southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3557625FFFDFF9CFBF1941DDEB2FBE0" name="Algeria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F3557625FFFDFF9CFE7F9403DFA3FBE0" box="[397,476,1087,1109]" name="Tunisia" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
. The above specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F3557625FFFDFF9CFD0F9403DD4DFBE0" box="[765,818,1087,1109]" name="Chad" pageId="9" pageNumber="1170">Chad</collectingCountry>
represents a new country record. The currently known distribution is illustrated in Map 2.
</paragraph>
